# 6. ４人で音楽を

Shiho: Okay, that's all the mics...
Shiho: I should be able to head out now that I've finished putting everything away.
Manager: Nice work, Hinomori. Thanks for helping out again today.
Shiho: Oh, hi. Thank you for having me again.
Manager: How's your band been doing lately? You must be really busy now that you've had your big debut.
Shiho: Yes, though things have been ramping up slowly.
Shiho: And I'm sorry about all the trouble I've been causing you. I just haven't been able to work as much...
Manager: Ah, don't worry about that.
Manager: I'm just happy that I get to see someone I know become a success! Let me know if you have any questions regarding shifts and stuff.
Shiho: Okay, thank you.
???: Is the manager here?
Shiho: ...! Iori! Mio...!
Mio: Oh, Hinomori...! Long time no see.
Iori: I'm glad we bumped into each other. We didn't know you were scheduled to work today.
Manager: Wait, you both came? Is something the matter?
Iori: Actually, yeah. We wanted to discuss something regarding our next show.
Iori: But if Hinomori's on her way out, mind if we talked to her for a bit first?
Shiho: Huh? Me?
Manager: Haha, sure thing. I'll be taking care of some stuff over there, so let me know once you're done chatting.
Manager: See you later, Hinomori.
Shiho: Oh... O-Okay, see you.
Mio: Umm... Sorry, we didn't mean to startle you or anything...
Shiho: It's okay. I was just a bit surprised, is all.
Shiho: So, umm...
Iori: Hehe. Try to relax.
Iori: And congratulations on your big debut, Hinomori.
Shiho: Oh...
Shiho: Thank you very much...
Mio: Hehe. You don't know how much Iori's been wanting to congratulate you, Hinomori.
Mio: I told her that she should just shoot you a message, but she was so adamant about congratulating you in person.
Iori: Hey, she doesn't need to know all that.
Shiho: I had no idea. Again, thank you...
Iori: No, Hinomori, don't laugh.
Iori: You girls made a really good song. Your bass sounded so alive.
Iori: I guess it's proof that Leo/need allows you to shine at your brightest.
Shiho: I appreciate you saying that.
Shiho: And thank you again, for everything...
Iori: Hm?
Shiho: We wouldn't have been able to go pro if it weren't for you two, Iori.
Shiho: If you hadn't invited me to join your band back then, I don't think we would've ever decided to try to go pro.
Shiho: Because me leaving Leo/need had become a real possibility...
Mio: Hinomori...
Shiho: So, thank you.
Iori: I see... That certainly was a path you could've taken.
Iori: But even if you did decide to leave, I doubt it would've been easy for you to actually do it.
Shiho: Huh?
Iori: I mean, deep down, Hinomori, you've always wanted to keep playing music with your friends, right?
Iori: It was written all over your face back then.
Shiho: Yeah, maybe you're right...
Iori: Anyway, the hard part starts here.
Iori: Because you have to keep getting better in order to stay competitive. And we're not about to let you hog all the glory.
Shiho: Right!!
Shiho: We promise to keep doing our best to keep up with STANDOUT.
Shiho: (Phew... It's gotten pretty late.)
Shiho: Oh...
Ichika's Voice: <——♪ ——♪>
Shiho: (Our song's playing again... It's coming from that billboard.)
Shiho: (The music video turned out so well. We all look so serious...)
Iori: But even if you did decide to leave, I doubt it would've been easy for you to actually do it.
Iori: I mean, deep down, Hinomori, you've always wanted to keep playing music with your friends, right?
Iori: It was written all over your face back then.
Shiho: ...
Shiho: (She's right.)
Shiho: (When I was in junior high, I tried forming a band with other people... But it didn't go well.)
Shiho: (I'd convinced myself somewhere along the way that my bandmates had to be as serious as I was.)
Shiho: (Otherwise, we wouldn't be able to succeed.)
Shiho: (That's why... When Ichika and Saki wanted to get the band back together, I thought it wouldn't work out.)
Shiho: (I mean, they didn't initially have careers as musicians on their radar.)
Shiho: (But...)
Shiho: Don't come crying to me later saying you can't hack it.
Shiho: Join your band, yeah. If that's okay with you.
Shiho: (In the end, I realized that I wanted to keep playing with them.)
Shiho: (My desire to go pro had always been strong...)
Shiho: (But so was my desire to keep playing with them.)
???: <Umm... Shiho...?>
Shiho: Huh? Who just...?
Shiho: Oh, KAITO...! Is something the matter?
KAITO: <I was going to ask if you'd come over and play your bass with me...>
KAITO: <But I'm sorry... I overheard your conversation at the live house.>
Shiho: Oh, I see.
Shiho: But that's okay. Nothing we talked about needed to stay hidden or anything.
KAITO: <Really? Thank goodness...>
Shiho: More importantly, I do feel like practicing, so would you like to join me?
KAITO: <Wait, now? But it's getting pretty late...>
Shiho: I know. But I really feel like playing my bass right now. Just for a little bit?
KAITO: <Okay, understood... Then, I'll meet you in SEKAI and... Oh...>
KAITO: <That reminds me... Have you heard about the new area that appeared over here...?>
Shiho: What new area...?
